# Re-importing required libraries and running the clustering
from PIL import Image
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from sklearn.cluster import KMeans

# Load the new simple image
image_path = 'simple image clustering.webp'
image = Image.open(image_path)
image = np.array(image)

# Reshape the image to be a list of pixels
pixels = image.reshape((-1, 3))

# Apply K-means clustering with 3 clusters
kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=3)
kmeans.fit(pixels)

# Replace each pixel value with its center value
centers = np.uint8(kmeans.cluster_centers_)
segmented_image = centers[kmeans.labels_.flatten()]

# Reshape the segmented image to the original image shape
segmented_image = segmented_image.reshape(image.shape)

# Display the original and clustered images
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))

# Original Image
plt.subplot(1, 2, 1)
plt.title('Original Image')
plt.imshow(image)
plt.axis('off')

# K-means Clustered Image
plt.subplot(1, 2, 2)
plt.title('K-means Clustered Image with 3 Clusters')
plt.imshow(segmented_image)
plt.axis('off')

plt.show()

from sklearn.cluster import KMeans
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import cv2

# Load the image
image_path = 'K-mean(clustering).webp'
image = cv2.imread(image_path)
image = cv2.cvtColor(image, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)

# Reshape the image to be a list of pixels
pixels = image.reshape((-1, 3))

# Apply K-means clustering
kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=5)
kmeans.fit(pixels)

# Replace each pixel value with its center value
centers = np.uint8(kmeans.cluster_centers_)
segmented_image = centers[kmeans.labels_.flatten()]

# Reshape the segmented image to the original image shape
segmented_image = segmented_image.reshape(image.shape)

# Display the original and clustered images
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))

# Original Image
plt.subplot(1, 2, 1)
plt.title('Original Image')
plt.imshow(image)
plt.axis('off')

# K-means Clustered Image
plt.subplot(1, 2, 2)
plt.title('K-means Clustered Image')
plt.imshow(segmented_image)
plt.axis('off')

plt.show()
